Environment variables:

LOGGER_PORT logger port to connect to

LOGGER_DIR sets the directory to which logs and checkpoints are dumped.

LOGGER_TAG sets the string that is appeneded to messages. Must not exceed
31 characters (32 including null-terminator). 

LOGGER_ROTATE_PERIOD_US sets the interval between checkpoints in microseconds.

LIBLOG_MICROBENCHMARKS makes liblog output timing info at program termination.

LIBLOG_DEBUG_LEVEL specified the debug output level. 0 or unspecified means no debug output.
